The paper deals with testing properties of Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves Fourier analysis and spectral graph theory, which are topics in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Information theory (cs.IT) is also mentioned in the abstract. The paper also discusses connections between testing properties of Boolean functions and graph properties, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and structural informatics (cs.SI).
